{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881409656,"sessionID":"ses_285386450ffeByI5JDjYc05Ahx","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac7c8220015tp2Q3Tp2Dj2dX","messageID":"msg_d7ac7b3ee001DhOvfE5eJcpkYV","sessionID":"ses_285386450ffeByI5JDjYc05Ahx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_d7f987e0033f4dd3b30c75bf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Design\n2: \n3: Source tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n4: \n5: ## Chart.yaml\n6: \n7: | Field | Value |\n8: |--------|--------|\n9: | `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n10: | `name` | `agentcube` |\n11: | `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n12: | `version` | `0.1.0` |\n13: | `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n14: \n15: ## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n16: \n17: | Path | Type | Default |\n18: |------|------|---------|\n19: | `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n20: | `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n21: | `fullnameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n22: | `redis.addr` | string | `\"\"` |\n23: | `redis.password` | string | `\"\"` |\n24: | `router.replicas` | int | `1` |\n25: | `router.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` |\n26: | `router.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n27: | `router.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n28: | `router.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n29: | `router.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n30: | `router.service.targetPort` | int | `8080` |\n31: | `router.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n32: | `router.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n33: | `router.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n34: | `router.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n35: | `router.config` | object | `{}` |\n36: | `router.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n37: | `router.serviceAccountName` | string | `\"\"` |\n38: | `router.rbac.create` | bool | `false` |\n39: | `workloadmanager.replicas` | int | `1` |\n40: | `workloadmanager.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` |\n41: | `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n42: | `workloadmanager.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n43: | `workloadmanager.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n44: | `workloadmanager.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n45: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n46: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n47: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n48: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n49: | `workloadmanager.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n50: | `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | bool | `false` |\n51: | `volcano.scheduler.replicas` | int | `1` |\n52: | `volcano.scheduler.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler` |\n53: | `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n54: | `volcano.scheduler.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n55: \n56: Comments in `values.yaml` state Redis settings “must be provided by the user during installation”; defaults are still empty strings.\n57: \n58: ## Template files (`manifests/charts/base/templates/`)\n59: \n60: ### `workloadmanager.yaml`\n61: \n62: | Kind | Name | Namespace | Notes |\n63: |------|------|-----------|--------|\n64: | `Deployment` | `workloadmanager` | `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` | `replicas`: `workloadmanager.replicas`; `serviceAccountName`: `workloadmanager`; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `workloadmanager`; image `repository:tag`; `imagePullPolicy`; port `http` → `workloadmanager.service.port`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef `metadata.namespace`), `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `REDIS_ADDR`, plus `workloadmanager.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, `--runtime-class-name=` (empty); **resources**: from values; **liveness/readiness**: HTTP GET `/health` on service port, delays 10s/10s and 5s/5s |\n65: | `Service` | `workloadmanager` | release ns | `type`: `workloadmanager.service.type`; port & `targetPort`: `workloadmanager.service.port`; selector `app: workloadmanager` |\n66: \n67: ### `agentcube-router.yaml`\n68: \n69: | Kind | Name | Notes |\n70: |------|------|--------|\n71: | `Deployment` | `agentcube-router` | `replicas`: `router.replicas`; **conditional** `serviceAccountName` if `router.serviceAccountName` non-empty; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `agentcube-router`; image from `router.image`; container port `router.service.targetPort`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef), `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` = `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, plus `router.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ router.service.targetPort }}`, `--debug`; **resources** from values; **liveness** `/health/live`, **readiness** `/health/ready` on targetPort, 1s initial, 2s period |\n72: | `Service` | `agentcube-router` | `type` `router.service.type`; `port` `router.service.port`, `targetPort` `router.service.targetPort`; selector `app: agentcube-router` |\n73: \n74: ### `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n75: \n76: | Kind | Name | Scope | Notes |\n77: |------|------|-------|--------|\n78: | `ServiceAccount` | `workloadmanager` | release namespace | — |\n79: | `ClusterRole` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | rules below |\n80: | `ClusterRoleBinding` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | binds `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` to `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in release namespace |\n81: \n82: ### `rbac-router.yaml`\n83: \n84: Rendered **only if** `router.rbac.create` is true.\n85: \n86: | Kind | Name pattern | Notes |\n87: |------|--------------|--------|\n88: | `ServiceAccount` | `{{ router.serviceAccountName \\| default \"agentcube-router\" }}` | release namespace |\n89: | `Role` | same as SA name | rules: `secrets` in `\"\"` apiGroup, full verb set `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n90: | `RoleBinding` | same | subject: SA above; `Role` ref same name |\n91: \n92: ### `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n93: \n94: Rendered **only if** `volcano.scheduler.enabled`.\n95: \n96: Creates (in order in file): `ServiceAccount/volcano-agent-scheduler`; `ConfigMap/volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap` with key `agent-scheduler.conf` (actions `allocate`, tiers predicates/nodeorder); `ClusterRole/volcano-agent-scheduler` (large rule set — see RBAC section); `ClusterRoleBinding/volcano-agent-scheduler-role`; `Service/volcano-agent-scheduler-service` (port 8080 metrics annotations); `Deployment/volcano-agent-scheduler` with `replicas` from `volcano.scheduler.replicas`, image from values, args including `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`, security contexts, volumes for config + emptyDir.\n97: \n98: ## RBAC rules (exact apiGroups / resources / verbs)\n99: \n100: ### ClusterRole `workloadmanager`\n101: \n102: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n103: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n104: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxes` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n105: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n106: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxtemplates` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n107: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n108: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n109: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n110: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n111: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/finalizers` | `update` |\n112: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes` | `get,list,watch` |\n113: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes/status` | `update,patch` |\n114: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch` |\n115: | `authentication.k8s.io` | `tokenreviews` | `create` |\n116: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n117: \n118: ### Role `router` (optional)\n119: \n120: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n121: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n122: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n123: \n124: ### ClusterRole `volcano-agent-scheduler` (when enabled)\n125: \n126: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n127: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n128: | `apiextensions.k8s.io` | `customresourcedefinitions` | `create,get,list,watch,delete` |\n129: | `\"\"` | `events` | `create,list,watch,update,patch` |\n130: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch,patch,delete` |\n131: | `\"\"` | `pods/status` | `update` |\n132: | `\"\"` | `pods/binding` | `create` |\n133: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumeclaims` | `list,watch,update` |\n134: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumes` | `list,watch,update` |\n135: | `\"\"` | `namespaces,services,replicationcontrollers` | `list,watch,get` |\n136: | `\"\"` | `resourcequotas` | `list,watch` |\n137: | `\"\"` | `nodes` | `get,list,watch,update,patch` |\n138: | `storage.k8s.io` | `storageclasses,csinodes,csidrivers,csistoragecapacities,volumeattachments` | `list,watch` |\n139: | `policy` | `poddisruptionbudgets` | `list,watch` |\n140: | `scheduling.k8s.io` | `priorityclasses` | `get,list,watch` |\n141: | `scheduling.incubator.k8s.io`, `scheduling.volcano.sh` | `podgroups` | `list,watch,update` |\n142: | `\"\"` | `configmaps` | `get,list,watch,create,delete,update` |\n143: | `apps` | `daemonsets,replicasets,statefulsets` | `list,watch,get` |\n144: | `coordination.k8s.io` | `leases` | `get,create,update,watch` |\n145: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch` |\n146: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims/status` | `update` |\n147: | `resource.k8s.io` | `deviceclasses,resourceslices` | `get,list,watch,create` |\n148: | `shard.volcano.sh` | `nodeshards` | `list,watch,get,update` |\n149: \n150: ## CRD definitions shipped (`manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n151: \n152: | File | CRD `metadata.name` | group | versions | scope | Notes |\n153: |------|---------------------|-------|----------|-------|--------|\n154: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` | `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` (served+storage); printer column Age | `Namespaced` | `openAPIV3Schema` includes root fields `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata`, `spec`, `status`. **spec.required**: `maxSessionDuration`, `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`, `targetPort`. **Key spec fields**: `maxSessionDuration` (string, default `8h`); `sessionTimeout` (string, default `15m`); `targetPort` (array of port objects: required `port`, `protocol` enum HTTP/HTTPS, optional `name`, `pathPrefix`); `podTemplate` (annotations, labels, nested `spec` = full PodSpec-shaped schema). **status**: conditions, etc. Annotation `controller-gen.kubebuilder.io/version: v0.17.2` |\n155: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` | `Namespaced` | **spec** includes `authMode` enum `picod|none` default `picod`; `maxSessionDuration` default `8h`; `sessionTimeout` default `15m`; `ports` (same TargetPort shape as above); `template` (image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, etc.); optional `warmPoolSize` int32. **spec.required**: `template`. **status**: `conditions`, `ready`; subresource `status`. Same controller-gen version annotation |\n156: \n157: ## Dockerfiles\n158: \n159: ### `docker/Dockerfile` (workloadmanager)\n160: \n161: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n162: |-------|------|---------|\n163: | builder | `golang:1.24.9-alpine` | `WORKDIR /workspace`; copy `go.mod`/`go.sum`; `go mod download`; copy `cmd/`, `pkg/`; build `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` with BuildKit cache mounts |\n164: | runtime | `alpine:3.19` | `apk add ca-certificates`; `WORKDIR /app`; copy binary; `adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver`; `USER apiserver`; `EXPOSE 8080`; `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]`; `CMD [\"--port=8080\"]` |\n165: \n166: Build args: `TARGETOS=linux`, `TARGETARCH` (implicit platform).\n167: \n168: ### `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n169: \n170: Same pattern as workloadmanager builder, plus `COPY client-go/ client-go/`; output binary `agentcube-router` from `./cmd/router`; runtime user `router` UID 1000; `CMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]`.\n171: \n172: ### `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n173: \n174: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n175: |-------|------|---------|\n176: | builder | `golang:1.24.4` | `WORKDIR /app`; copy mod files; download; `COPY . .`; build `picod` from `./cmd/picod` with `CGO_ENABLED=0` |\n177: | runtime | `ubuntu:24.04` | `apt-get install -y python3`; `WORKDIR /root/`; copy binary; **runs as root** (comment: chattr on pubkey + sandbox permissions); `ENTRYPOINT [\"./picod\"]` |\n178: \n179: ## Makefile — variables (key)\n180: \n181: | Variable | Default / definition |\n182: |----------|----------------------|\n183: | `HUB` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` |\n184: | `TAG` | `latest` |\n185: | `PROJECT_DIR` | directory of Makefile |\n186: | `GOBIN` | from `go env` |\n187: | `CONTAINER_TOOL` | `docker` |\n188: | `SHELL` | `/usr/bin/env bash -o pipefail` |\n189: | `LOCALBIN` | `$(shell pwd)/bin` |\n190: | `CONTROLLER_GEN` | `$(LOCALBIN)/controller-gen` |\n191: | `GOLANGCI_LINT` | `$(LOCALBIN)/golangci-lint` |\n192: | `CONTROLLER_TOOLS_VERSION` | `v0.17.2` |\n193: | `GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION` | `v1.64.1` |\n194: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` | `workloadmanager:latest` |\n195: | `ROUTER_IMAGE` | `agentcube-router:latest` |\n196: | `PICOD_IMAGE` | `picod:latest` |\n197: | `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `\"\"` |\n198: | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` | `agentcube-e2e` |\n199: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_REPO` | `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox.git` |\n200: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION` | `main` (Makefile comment; E2E script overrides — see CI design) |\n201: \n202: ## Makefile — targets\n203: \n204: | Target | Depends / notes |\n205: |--------|-----------------|\n206: | `all` | → `build` |\n207: | `help` | awk help from `##` comments |\n208: | `gen-crd` | `controller-gen`; `crd paths=./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` → `manifests/charts/base/crds` |\n209: | `generate` | `controller-gen object` + `gen-crd` + `go mod tidy` |\n210: | `gen-client` | `bash hack/update-codegen.sh`; `go mod tidy` |\n211: | `gen-all` | `generate` + `gen-client` |\n212: | `gen-check` | `gen-all` then `git diff --exit-code` |\n213: | `build` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` |\n214: | `build-agentd` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd` |\n215: | `build-router` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentcube-router ./cmd/router` |\n216: | `build-all` | `build` + `build-agentd` + `build-router` |\n217: | `run` | `go run ./cmd/workload-manager/main.go --port=8080 --ssh-username=sandbox --ssh-port=22` |\n218: | `run-local` | same with `--kubeconfig=${HOME}/.kube/config` |\n219: | `run-router` | `go run ./cmd/router/main.go --port=8080 --debug` |\n220: | `clean` | `rm -rf bin/` and root binaries |\n221: | `deps` | `go mod download`; `go mod tidy` |\n222: | `update-deps` | `go get -u ./...`; `go mod tidy` |\n223: | `test` | `go test -v ./...` |\n224: | `fmt` | `go fmt ./...` |\n225: | `vet` | `go vet ./...` |\n226: | `lint` | `$(GOLANGCI_LINT) run ./...` |\n227: | `gen-copyright` | `hack/update-copyright.sh` |\n228: | `install` | `build` + `sudo cp bin/workloadmanager /usr/local/bin/` |\n229: | `docker-build` | `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE) .` |\n230: | `docker-buildx` | buildx linux/amd64,arm64 |\n231: | `docker-buildx-push` | requires `IMAGE_REGISTRY`; buildx `--push` |\n232: | `docker-push` | tag+push workloadmanager |\n233: | `kind-load` | `kind load docker-image $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE)` |\n234: | `docker-build-router` / `docker-buildx-router` / `docker-buildx-push-router` / `docker-push-router` / `kind-load-router` | same pattern for router image |\n235: | `docker-build-picod` / `docker-buildx-picod` / `docker-buildx-push-picod` / `docker-push-picod` | same for picod |\n236: | `controller-gen` / `golangci-lint` | download via `go-install-tool` macro |\n237: | `e2e` | `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n238: | `e2e-clean` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n239: | `build-python-sdk` | copy `LICENSE` to `sdk-python`, `python3 -m build` in `sdk-python`, remove copied LICENSE |\n240: \n241: ## hack/ scripts\n242: \n243: | File | Purpose |\n244: |------|---------|\n245: | `hack/update-codegen.sh` | Runs `k8s.io/code-generator` **v0.34.1**: sources `kube_codegen.sh`, calls `kube::codegen::gen_client --with-watch --output-dir client-go --output-pkg github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go --boilerplate hack/boilerplate.go.txt --one-input-api runtime/v1alpha1` on `pkg/apis`; post-processes lister files with `sed` to append `.GroupResource()` for codeinterpreter/agentruntime resources |\n246: | `hack/update-copyright.sh` | Prepends Apache/Volcano boilerplate to `*.go` and `*.py` under git root (excluding vendor/venv) if missing “Copyright The Volcano Authors”; uses `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` / `hack/boilerplate.py.txt`; requires `sponge` (moreutils) |\n247: | `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` | Go file header template |\n248: | `hack/boilerplate.py.txt` | Python file header template |\n249: \n250: ## Helm / E2E reference command (from `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n251: \n252: Illustrative install used in E2E:\n253: \n254: ```bash\n255: helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n256:   --namespace \"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n257:   --create-namespace \\\n258:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n259:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n260:   --set workloadmanager.image.repository=\"workloadmanager\" \\\n261:   --set workloadmanager.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n262:   --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"},{\"name\":\"JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE\",\"value\":\"agentcube\"}]' \\\n263:   --set router.image.repository=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n264:   --set router.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n265:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n266:   --set router.serviceAccountName=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n267:   --set-json 'router.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"}]' \\\n268:   --wait\n269: ```\n270: \n271: Images are expected to be loaded into Kind with local names `workloadmanager:latest`, `agentcube-router:latest`, `picod:latest` after `make docker-build` variants.\n\n(End of file - total 271 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Design\n\nSource tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n\n## Chart.yaml\n\n| Field | Value |\n|--------|--------|\n| `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n| `name` | `agentcube` |\n| `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n| `version` | `0.1.0` |\n| `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n\n## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n\n| Path | Type | Default |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n| `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/design.md","time":{"start":1775881409630,"end":1775881409654}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881409659,"sessionID":"ses_285386450ffeByI5JDjYc05Ahx","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac7c336001IdoZGyA5ElXL2Z","messageID":"msg_d7ac7b3ee001DhOvfE5eJcpkYV","sessionID":"ses_285386450ffeByI5JDjYc05Ahx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_aa093ce6888a4a918beb8645","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `docker`  \n6: **Language:** Dockerfile  \n7: **Size:** S  \n8: **Type:** Multi-stage Docker build for Workload Manager, Router, and picod container images\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** deployment/spec.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-032.1: Workload Manager Dockerfile\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile` for building the Workload Manager container image using multi-stage build with separate build and runtime stages.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Build stage configuration\n21: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile` is built with repository root as context\n22: - **WHEN** the build stage runs\n23: - **THEN** it SHALL use `golang:1.21-alpine` as builder base image\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Go module cache optimization\n26: - **GIVEN** go.mod and go.sum files exist\n27: - **WHEN** the build stage copies dependencies\n28: - **THEN** it SHALL copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first and run `go mod download` before copying source code\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Workload Manager binary compilation\n31: - **GIVEN** source code is copied to builder\n32: - **WHEN** build runs\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL compile with `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o /workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Runtime stage base image\n36: - **GIVEN** build stage completes\n37: - **WHEN** runtime stage begins\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL use `alpine:3.19` as minimal runtime base image\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Non-root user creation\n41: - **GIVEN** runtime stage starts\n42: - **WHEN** image is prepared\n43: - **THEN** it SHALL create non-root user `apiserver` with UID 1000\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Binary copy to runtime image\n46: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager binary is built\n47: - **WHEN** runtime stage copies artifacts\n48: - **THEN** it SHALL copy binary from builder stage to `/workloadmanager`\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Container port exposure\n51: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n52: - **WHEN** container runs\n53: - **THEN** it SHALL expose port 8080\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Default command configuration\n56: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n57: - **WHEN** container starts without override\n58: - **THEN** it SHALL run `/workloadmanager` as entrypoint\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### REQ-032.2: Router Dockerfile\n63: \n64: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile.router` for building the Router container image using multi-stage build with separate build and runtime stages.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Build stage configuration\n67: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.router` is built with repository root as context\n68: - **WHEN** the build stage runs\n69: - **THEN** it SHALL use `golang:1.21-alpine` as builder base image\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Go module cache optimization\n72: - **GIVEN** go.mod and go.sum files exist\n73: - **WHEN** the build stage copies dependencies\n74: - **THEN** it SHALL copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first and run `go mod download` before copying source code\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Router binary compilation\n77: - **GIVEN** source code is copied to builder\n78: - **WHEN** build runs\n79: - **THEN** it SHALL compile with `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o /router ./cmd/router`\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Runtime stage base image\n82: - **GIVEN** build stage completes\n83: - **WHEN** runtime stage begins\n84: - **THEN** it SHALL use `alpine:3.19` as minimal runtime base image\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: Non-root user creation\n87: - **GIVEN** runtime stage starts\n88: - **WHEN** image is prepared\n89: - **THEN** it SHALL create non-root user `router` with UID 1000\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Binary copy to runtime image\n92: - **GIVEN** router binary is built\n93: - **WHEN** runtime stage copies artifacts\n94: - **THEN** it SHALL copy binary from builder stage to `/router`\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Container port exposure\n97: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n98: - **WHEN** container runs\n99: - **THEN** it SHALL expose port 8080\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: Default command configuration\n102: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n103: - **WHEN** container starts without override\n104: - **THEN** it SHALL run `/router` as entrypoint\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ### REQ-032.3: Picod Dockerfile\n109: \n110: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile.picod` for building the picod container image using multi-stage build with separate build and runtime stages.\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Build stage configuration\n113: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.picod` is built with repository root as context\n114: - **WHEN** the build stage runs\n115: - **THEN** it SHALL use `golang:1.21-alpine` as builder base image\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Go module cache optimization\n118: - **GIVEN** go.mod and go.sum files exist\n119: - **WHEN** the build stage copies dependencies\n120: - **THEN** it SHALL copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first and run `go mod download` before copying source code\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: Picod binary compilation\n123: - **GIVEN** source code is copied to builder\n124: - **WHEN** build runs\n125: - **THEN** it SHALL compile with `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o /picod ./cmd/picod`\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Runtime stage base image\n128: - **GIVEN** build stage completes\n129: - **WHEN** runtime stage begins\n130: - **THEN** it SHALL use `alpine:3.19` as minimal runtime base image\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Non-root user creation\n133: - **GIVEN** runtime stage starts\n134: - **WHEN** image is prepared\n135: - **THEN** it SHALL create non-root user `picod` with UID 1000\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: Binary copy to runtime image\n138: - **GIVEN** picod binary is built\n139: - **WHEN** runtime stage copies artifacts\n140: - **THEN** it SHALL copy binary from builder stage to `/picod`\n141: \n142: #### Scenario: Container port exposure\n143: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n144: - **WHEN** container runs\n145: - **THEN** it SHALL expose port 8080\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: Default command configuration\n148: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n149: - **WHEN** container starts without override\n150: - **THEN** it SHALL run `/picod` as entrypoint\n151: \n152: ---\n153: \n154: ### REQ-032.4: Multi-stage Build Optimization\n155: \n156: **Requirement:** The system SHALL optimize Docker images for size and security through multi-stage build patterns.\n157: \n158: #### Scenario: Minimal runtime image\n159: - **GIVEN** multi-stage build completes\n160: - **WHEN** final image size is measured\n161: - **THEN** it SHALL be under 50MB for each component (Workload Manager, Router, picod)\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: No build tools in runtime\n164: - **GIVEN** runtime stage completes\n165: - **WHEN** image is inspected\n166: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT contain go compiler, git, or build dependencies\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: Static binary linkage\n169: - **GIVEN** CGO_ENABLED=0 is set during build\n170: - **WHEN** binary runs in runtime stage\n171: - **THEN** it SHALL have no dynamic library dependencies\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Alpine base image\n174: - **GIVEN** runtime stage uses alpine:3.19\n175: - **WHEN** image is scanned for vulnerabilities\n176: - **THEN** it SHALL have minimal CVE surface compared to Debian-based images\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ### REQ-032.5: Security Best Practices\n181: \n182: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement container security best practices in all Dockerfiles.\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: Non-root user execution\n185: - **GIVEN** container starts\n186: - **WHEN** process runs\n187: - **THEN** it SHALL run as non-root user (UID 1000)\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: Read-only filesystem compatibility\n190: - **GIVEN** container runs with read-only root filesystem\n191: - **WHEN** application needs temporary storage\n192: - **THEN** it SHALL use `/tmp` volume mount if needed\n193: \n194: #### Scenario: No secrets in image\n195: - **GIVEN** Dockerfile is built\n196: - **WHEN** image layers are inspected\n197: - **THEN** they SHALL NOT contain hardcoded credentials, tokens, or API keys\n198: \n199: #### Scenario: Minimal attack surface\n200: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n201: - **WHEN** shell access is attempted\n202: - **THEN** image MAY exclude `/bin/sh` to prevent shell injection (optional hardening)\n203: \n204: ---\n205: \n206: ### REQ-032.6: Build Context and .dockerignore\n207: \n208: **Requirement:** The system SHALL use efficient build context by excluding unnecessary files via `.dockerignore`.\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: Exclude .git directory\n211: - **GIVEN** `.dockerignore` exists\n212: - **WHEN** build context is sent to Docker daemon\n213: - **THEN** `.git/` directory SHALL be excluded\n214: \n215: #### Scenario: Exclude build artifacts\n216: - **GIVEN** `.dockerignore` exists\n217: - **WHEN** build context is sent\n218: - **THEN** `bin/`, `pkg/`, and `*_test.go` files SHALL be excluded from context\n219: \n220: #### Scenario: Exclude development files\n221: - **GIVEN** `.dockerignore` exists\n222: - **WHEN** build context is sent\n223: - **THEN** `.md` files (except README if needed), `.gitignore`, and editor files SHALL be excluded\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Include only required files\n226: - **GIVEN** `.dockerignore` is configured\n227: - **WHEN** build runs\n228: - **THEN** context SHALL include only: `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `cmd/`, `pkg/`, and any required configs\n229: \n230: ---\n231: \n232: ### REQ-032.7: Makefile Integration\n233: \n234: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for building all three Docker images.\n235: \n236: #### Scenario: Build Workload Manager image\n237: - **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-build-workloadmanager` target\n238: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-workloadmanager` runs\n239: - **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged `workloadmanager:latest` using `docker/Dockerfile`\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: Build Router image\n242: - **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-build-router` target\n243: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-router` runs\n244: - **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged `router:latest` using `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n245: \n246: #### Scenario: Build picod image\n247: - **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-build-picod` target\n248: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-picod` runs\n249: - **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged `picod:latest` using `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: Build all images\n252: - **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-build-all` target\n253: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-all` runs\n254: - **THEN** it SHALL build all three images sequentially\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: Push Workload Manager image\n257: - **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-push-workloadmanager` target with `REGISTRY` variable\n258: - **WHEN** `make docker-push-workloadmanager REGISTRY=registry.example.com` runs\n259: - **THEN** it SHALL tag and push image to `registry.example.com/workloadmanager:latest`\n260: \n261: #### Scenario: Push all images\n262: - **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-push-all` target with `REGISTRY` variable\n263: - **WHEN** `make docker-push-all REGISTRY=registry.example.com` runs\n264: - **THEN** it SHALL tag and push all three images to specified registry\n265: \n266: ---\n267: \n268: ## Data Types\n269: \n270: ```dockerfile\n271: # Docker build arguments (common to all Dockerfiles)\n272: ARG GO_VERSION=1.21\n273: ARG ALPINE_VERSION=3.19\n274: ARG TARGETARCH=amd64\n275: \n276: # Labels for image metadata\n277: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.title=\"<component>\"\n278: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.description=\"AgentCube <component> component\"\n279: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.vendor=\"AgentCube\"\n280: ```\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ## File Structure\n285: \n286: ```\n287: docker/\n288: ├── Dockerfile           # Workload Manager image\n289: ├── Dockerfile.router    # Router image\n290: ├── Dockerfile.picod     # Picod image\n291: └── .dockerignore        # Build context exclusions (shared or per-Dockerfile)\n292: ```\n293: \n294: ---\n295: \n296: ## Make Targets\n297: \n298: | Target | Description |\n299: |--------|-------------|\n300: | `docker-build-workloadmanager` | Build Workload Manager image |\n301: | `docker-build-router` | Build Router image |\n302: | `docker-build-picod` | Build picod image |\n303: | `docker-build-all` | Build all three images |\n304: | `docker-push-workloadmanager` | Push Workload Manager image to registry |\n305: | `docker-push-router` | Push Router image to registry |\n306: | `docker-push-picod` | Push picod image to registry |\n307: | `docker-push-all` | Push all images to registry |\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ## Environment Variables\n312: \n313: | Variable | Component | Purpose | Default |\n314: |----------|-----------|---------|---------|\n315: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Workload Manager, Router | Redis server address | - |\n316: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Workload Manager, Router | Redis authentication | \"\" |\n317: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Router | Workload Manager endpoint | - |\n318: | `PORT` | All | HTTP listen port | 8080 |\n319: \n320: ---\n321: \n322: ## Acceptance Checklist\n323: \n324: - [ ] `docker/Dockerfile` — Workload Manager multi-stage build\n325: - [ ] `docker/Dockerfile.router` — Router multi-stage build\n326: - [ ] `docker/Dockerfile.picod` — Picod multi-stage build\n327: - [ ] `docker/.dockerignore` — Build context optimization\n328: - [ ] Make targets for building all three images\n329: - [ ] Make targets for pushing images to registry\n330: - [ ] Non-root user in all runtime images\n331: - [ ] Alpine 3.19 base for minimal image size\n332: - [ ] CGO disabled for static binaries\n333: - [ ] Port 8080 exposed in all images\n334: - [ ] Image size under 50MB each\n335: - [ ] OCI labels for image metadata\n336: - [ ] Go module cache optimization (go.mod copied first)\n337: \n338: ---\n339: \n340: ## Open Questions\n341: \n342: 1. Should Dockerfiles support multi-architecture builds (ARM64, AMD64) via `--platform` flag?\n343: 2. Should health check instructions (`HEALTHCHECK`) be added to Dockerfiles?\n344: 3. Should distroless images be used instead of Alpine for enhanced security?\n345: 4. Should build version/commit be injected into images via `ARG` at build time?\n346: \n347: (End of file)\n\n(End of file - total 347 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `docker`  \n**Language:** Dockerfile  \n**Size:** S  \n**Type:** Multi-stage Docker build for Workload Manager, Router, and picod container images\n\n**Base Specs:** deployment/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-032.1: Workload Manager Dockerfile\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile` for building the Workload Manager container image using multi-stage build with separate build and runtime stages.\n\n#### Scenario: Build stage configuration","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775881409627,"end":1775881409658}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881409678,"sessionID":"ses_285386450ffeByI5JDjYc05Ahx","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac7cd32001C23LyURqORl95L","messageID":"msg_d7ac7b3ee001DhOvfE5eJcpkYV","sessionID":"ses_285386450ffeByI5JDjYc05Ahx","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_96b52c1d211b4a1d9bbadfcd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"find /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z -name \"*.md\" | grep -i \"ar-032\" 2>/dev/null","description":"Find AR-032 related files"},"output":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-032/index.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md\n","metadata":{"output":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-032/index.md\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md\n","exit":0,"description":"Find AR-032 related files","truncated":false},"title":"Find AR-032 related files","time":{"start":1775881409634,"end":1775881409676}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775881409704,"sessionID":"ses_285386450ffeByI5JDjYc05Ahx","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac7d48e001ZAiQSYgXUpLC4N","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7ac7b3ee001DhOvfE5eJcpkYV","sessionID":"ses_285386450ffeByI5JDjYc05Ahx","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":22620,"input":6,"output":369,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":6754,"read":15491}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775881411975,"sessionID":"ses_285386450ffeByI5JDjYc05Ahx","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac7dd84001D5tf9M7996s5uX","messageID":"msg_d7ac7d4c3001CyJ8FdRIN02qzu","sessionID":"ses_285386450ffeByI5JDjYc05Ahx","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881416991,"sessionID":"ses_285386450ffeByI5JDjYc05Ahx","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac7e557001WzOZg4a2ZcpUYo","messageID":"msg_d7ac7d4c3001CyJ8FdRIN02qzu","sessionID":"ses_285386450ffeByI5JDjYc05Ahx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ce7aaf3e54f64d508c623cb7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Deploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Helm chart installation\n9: The system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n13: - **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n14: - **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\n17: The system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n20: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values\n21: - **WHEN** pods for `workloadmanager` and `agentcube-router` start\n22: - **THEN** each container SHALL have environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` populated from those values\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Workload Manager deployment shape\n25: The system SHALL deploy Workload Manager as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `workloadmanager` with replica count, container image, service type/port, resource requests/limits, health probes, and optional `extraEnv` driven from `values.yaml`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Default replica and service exposure\n28: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n29: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n30: - **THEN** the Workload Manager `Deployment` SHALL use `workloadmanager.replicas` (default 1), expose HTTP on `workloadmanager.service.port` (default 8080), and use liveness/readiness HTTP GET `/health` on that port\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Router deployment shape\n33: The system SHALL deploy the Router as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `agentcube-router` with replica count, image, `ClusterIP` service mapping `port`→`targetPort`, resource requests/limits, optional dedicated `serviceAccountName`, and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` pointing at the in-cluster Workload Manager service.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router reaches Workload Manager by DNS\n36: - **GIVEN** release namespace `N` and Workload Manager service port `P` from values\n37: - **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL have `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` set to `http://workloadmanager.N.svc.cluster.local:P` and container args including `--port=<targetPort>` and `--debug`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Workload Manager ClusterRole permissions\n41: The system SHALL create a `ServiceAccount` `workloadmanager`, a `ClusterRole` `workloadmanager`, and `ClusterRoleBinding` `workloadmanager` granting the rules required for agent-sandbox, AgentCube runtime CRDs, core workloads, auth, and secrets.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Binding ties SA to cluster role\n44: - **GIVEN** chart installation in namespace `N`\n45: - **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n46: - **THEN** subject `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in namespace `N` SHALL be bound to `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` via `ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Optional Router namespace Role\n49: The system SHALL optionally create namespace-scoped `ServiceAccount`, `Role`, and `RoleBinding` for the Router when `router.rbac.create` is true, granting secret management in that namespace.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: RBAC off by default\n52: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: false`\n53: - **WHEN** the chart renders templates\n54: - **THEN** Router optional RBAC manifests SHALL NOT be emitted\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: RBAC on with named service account\n57: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` and `router.serviceAccountName` set (or defaulted by template to `agentcube-router`)\n58: - **WHEN** the chart is applied\n59: - **THEN** Router pods MAY use that `serviceAccountName` and the Role SHALL allow verbs on `secrets` in the release namespace\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Optional Volcano agent scheduler\n62: The system SHALL optionally deploy Volcano agent scheduler resources (ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment) when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Scheduler disabled\n65: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (default)\n66: - **WHEN** templates render\n67: - **THEN** no Volcano scheduler objects SHALL be created\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: CRDs shipped with the chart\n70: The system SHALL ship `CustomResourceDefinition` manifests for `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters` under the chart `crds/` directory so Helm installs them with the chart lifecycle.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: CRD group and scope\n73: - **GIVEN** chart path `manifests/charts/base`\n74: - **WHEN** CRD YAML is applied\n75: - **THEN** both CRDs SHALL use API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, and `scope: Namespaced`\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Docker images for core binaries\n78: The system SHALL provide Dockerfiles to build three images: Workload Manager (`docker/Dockerfile`), Router (`docker/Dockerfile.router`), and picod (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`).\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Multi-stage Go build for control plane\n81: - **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n82: - **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile` (or `Dockerfile.router`) runs\n83: - **THEN** the image SHALL compile the respective Go binary with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and run it from Alpine 3.19 as a non-root user (`apiserver` UID 1000 or `router` UID 1000) exposing port 8080\n84: \n85: ### Requirement: Makefile build targets\n86: The system SHALL expose Make targets to build binaries (`build`, related targets), run tests (`test`), build/push Docker images (`docker-*`), run code generation (`generate`, `gen-crd`, `gen-client`, `gen-all`, `gen-check`), and run E2E (`e2e`, `e2e-clean`).\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Default `make` builds workload manager\n89: - **GIVEN** Go toolchain and generated code prerequisites\n90: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make` (default `all` → `build`)\n91: - **THEN** `bin/workloadmanager` SHALL be produced from `./cmd/workload-manager` after `generate`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: E2E entrypoint\n94: - **GIVEN** Kind, kubectl, Docker, Helm, and curl available\n95: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make e2e`\n96: - **THEN** the repository SHALL execute `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` which provisions the cluster (unless skipped), deploys dependencies, and runs Go and Python E2E tests\n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Specification\n\n## Purpose\nDeploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Helm chart installation\nThe system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n\n#### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n- **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n- **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n\n### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\nThe system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n\n#### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n- **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/spec.md","time":{"start":1775881416972,"end":1775881416989}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881417005,"sessionID":"ses_285386450ffeByI5JDjYc05Ahx","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac7dfed001RkGOLvsSJ7M2kt","messageID":"msg_d7ac7d4c3001CyJ8FdRIN02qzu","sessionID":"ses_285386450ffeByI5JDjYc05Ahx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_93b6304344454eec9ebb5cd9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: 本提案实现 AgentCube 项目的 Dockerfile 多阶段构建，为 Workload Manager、Router、Volcano Agent Scheduler 三个核心组件提供独立的容器镜像构建能力。该 Dockerfile 是 AgentCube 控制平面组件容器化的基础，支撑 Helm Chart 部署和 Kubernetes 运行时环境。\n6: \n7: 目标是：\n8: \n9: 1. **多阶段构建优化** - 使用多阶段构建减少最终镜像体积，仅包含运行必需的二进制文件和配置\n10: 2. **三镜像分离** - 为 Workload Manager、Router、Volcano Agent Scheduler 分别构建独立镜像，支持差异化部署\n11: 3. **最小化攻击面** - 基于 distroless 或 alpine 基础镜像，减少安全漏洞风险\n12: 4. **构建可复用** - 统一的 Dockerfile 模板支持本地构建、CI/CD 流水线、多架构支持\n13: 5. **环境一致性** - 确保开发、测试、生产环境的镜像构建行为一致\n14: 6. **版本可追溯** - 镜像标签与 Git commit/Tag 关联，支持版本追踪和回滚\n15: \n16: 本提案基于 deployment/design.md 和 deployment/spec.md 的规范，遵循 Docker 多阶段构建最佳实践。\n17: \n18: ## Scope\n19: \n20: **Module:** docker  \n21: **Language:** Dockerfile  \n22: **Size:** S\n23: \n24: 本 AR 包含：\n25: \n26: - **包含内容：**\n27:   - Dockerfile.workloadmanager - Workload Manager 镜像构建\n28:   - Dockerfile.router - Router 镜像构建\n29:   - Dockerfile.volcano-agent-scheduler - Volcano Agent Scheduler 镜像构建\n30:   - .dockerignore 文件 - 构建上下文忽略规则\n31:   - Makefile 构建目标 - 简化镜像构建命令\n32:   - 镜像验证脚本 - 验证镜像大小、层数、安全性\n33:   - 构建文档和使用示例\n34: \n35: - **不包含内容：**\n36:   - Helm Chart 模板（由 AR-030 管理）\n37:   - Kubernetes 部署配置\n38:   - CI/CD 流水线配置\n39:   - 镜像仓库推送逻辑\n40: \n41: ## Current State Analysis\n42: \n43: ### 现有构建状态\n44: \n45: 根据项目结构 `cmd/` 目录：\n46: - `cmd/agentcube/` - Workload Manager 源码（Go）\n47: - `cmd/agentcube-admin/` - 管理工具（Go）\n48: - `cmd/agentcube-proxy/` - 代理服务（Go）\n49: - `cmd/agentcube-shell/` - Shell 工具（Go）\n50: - `cmd/agentd/` - Agent Daemon（Go，已有二进制文件）\n51: - `cmd/cli/` - CLI 工具（Python）\n52: \n53: 当前无 Dockerfile，缺少容器化构建能力。\n54: \n55: ### 参考设计规范\n56: \n57: 根据 `deployment/design.md` 和 `deployment/spec.md`：\n58: \n59: **镜像要求：**\n60: - Workload Manager: 基于 Go 二进制文件，暴露 8080 端口\n61: - Router: 基于 Go 二进制文件，暴露 8080 端口\n62: - Volcano Agent Scheduler: 基于 Go 二进制文件，暴露 8080 端口（metrics）\n63: \n64: **基础镜像要求：**\n65: - 生产镜像：使用 gcr.io/distroless/static-debian11 或 alpine:3.18\n66: - 构建镜像：使用 golang:1.21-bookworm\n67: \n68: **镜像标签规范：**\n69: - latest - 最新开发版本\n70: - <version> - 语义化版本（如 0.1.0）\n71: - <commit-sha> - Git commit SHA\n72: \n73: ### 差距分析\n74: \n75: 1. **缺少 Dockerfile** - 无任何 Dockerfile，无法构建容器镜像\n76: 2. **缺少构建优化** - 未使用多阶段构建，镜像体积可能过大\n77: 3. **缺少安全加固** - 未使用 distroless 或最小化基础镜像\n78: 4. **缺少构建自动化** - 无 Makefile 构建目标或脚本\n79: \n80: ### deployment/spec.md 关键要求\n81: \n82: 1. **镜像分离** - 每个组件独立镜像，避免耦合\n83: 2. **端口暴露** - Workload Manager 8080, Router 8080, Scheduler 8080 (metrics)\n84: 3. **环境变量** - 支持 REDIS_ADDR, REDIS_PASSWORD, AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE 等\n85: 4. **健康检查** - Docker HEALTHCHECK 指令配置\n86: 5. **非 root 用户** - 生产镜像以非 root 用户运行\n87: \n88: ## Proposed Changes\n89: \n90: ### 1. 目录结构\n91: \n92: ```\n93: docker/\n94: ├── .dockerignore                       # 构建上下文忽略\n95: ├── Dockerfile.workloadmanager          # Workload Manager Dockerfile\n96: ├── Dockerfile.router                   # Router Dockerfile\n97: ├── Dockerfile.volcano-agent-scheduler  # Volcano Agent Scheduler Dockerfile\n98: ├── Makefile                            # 构建目标\n99: ├── validate.sh                         # 镜像验证脚本\n100: └── README.md                           # 构建说明文档\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ### 2. .dockerignore\n104: \n105: ```dockerignore\n106: # .dockerignore\n107: # Build context ignores\n108: \n109: # Git\n110: .git\n111: .gitignore\n112: \n113: # Build artifacts\n114: bin/\n115: dist/\n116: *.out\n117: \n118: # Dependencies\n119: vendor/\n120: \n121: # IDE\n122: .idea/\n123: .vscode/\n124: *.swp\n125: *.swo\n126: \n127: # Documentation\n128: *.md\n129: !README.md\n130: \n131: # Tests\n132: testing/\n133: *_test.go\n134: \n135: # Docker\n136: docker/\n137: Dockerfile*\n138: \n139: # Helm\n140: manifests/\n141: \n142: # Python\n143: __pycache__/\n144: *.pyc\n145: .pytest_cache/\n146: \n147: # Misc\n148: .DS_Store\n149: Thumbs.db\n150: ```\n151: \n152: ### 3. Workload Manager Dockerfile\n153: \n154: ```dockerfile\n155: # docker/Dockerfile.workloadmanager\n156: # Multi-stage build for Workload Manager\n157: \n158: # Stage 1: Build\n159: FROM golang:1.21-bookworm AS builder\n160: \n161: WORKDIR /build\n162: \n163: # Copy go mod files\n164: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n165: RUN go mod download\n166: \n167: # Copy source code\n168: COPY cmd/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n169: COPY pkg ./pkg\n170: \n171: # Build the binary\n172: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build \\\n173:     -ldflags=\"-w -s\" \\\n174:     -o /build/workloadmanager \\\n175:     ./cmd/agentcube\n176: \n177: # Stage 2: Runtime (distroless)\n178: FROM gcr.io/distroless/static-debian11:nonroot AS runtime\n179: \n180: # Copy binary from builder\n181: COPY --from=builder /build/workloadmanager /workloadmanager\n182: \n183: # Set non-root user\n184: USER nonroot:nonroot\n185: \n186: # Set working directory\n187: WORKDIR /\n188: \n189: # Expose port\n190: EXPOSE 8080\n191: \n192: # Health check\n193: HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n194:     CMD [\"/workloadmanager\", \"--health\"]\n195: \n196: # Entrypoint\n197: ENTRYPOINT [\"/workloadmanager\"]\n198: CMD [\"--port=8080\"]\n199: ```\n200: \n201: ### 4. Router Dockerfile\n202: \n203: ```dockerfile\n204: # docker/Dockerfile.router\n205: # Multi-stage build for Router\n206: \n207: # Stage 1: Build\n208: FROM golang:1.21-bookworm AS builder\n209: \n210: WORKDIR /build\n211: \n212: # Copy go mod files\n213: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n214: RUN go mod download\n215: \n216: # Copy source code\n217: COPY cmd/agentcube-proxy ./cmd/agentcube-proxy\n218: COPY pkg ./pkg\n219: \n220: # Build the binary\n221: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build \\\n222:     -ldflags=\"-w -s\" \\\n223:     -o /build/router \\\n224:     ./cmd/agentcube-proxy\n225: \n226: # Stage 2: Runtime (distroless)\n227: FROM gcr.io/distroless/static-debian11:nonroot AS runtime\n228: \n229: # Copy binary from builder\n230: COPY --from=builder /build/router /router\n231: \n232: # Set non-root user\n233: USER nonroot:nonroot\n234: \n235: # Set working directory\n236: WORKDIR /\n237: \n238: # Expose port\n239: EXPOSE 8080\n240: \n241: # Health check\n242: HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n243:     CMD [\"/router\", \"--health\"]\n244: \n245: # Entrypoint\n246: ENTRYPOINT [\"/router\"]\n247: CMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]\n248: ```\n249: \n250: ### 5. Volcano Agent Scheduler Dockerfile\n251: \n252: ```dockerfile\n253: # docker/Dockerfile.volcano-agent-scheduler\n254: # Multi-stage build for Volcano Agent Scheduler\n255: \n256: # Stage 1: Build\n257: FROM golang:1.21-bookworm AS builder\n258: \n259: WORKDIR /build\n260: \n261: # Copy go mod files\n262: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n263: RUN go mod download\n264: \n265: # Copy source code\n266: COPY cmd/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n267: COPY pkg ./pkg\n268: \n269: # Build the binary\n270: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build \\\n271:     -ldflags=\"-w -s\" \\\n272:     -o /build/volcano-agent-scheduler \\\n273:     ./cmd/agentd\n274: \n275: # Stage 2: Runtime (distroless)\n276: FROM gcr.io/distroless/static-debian11:nonroot AS runtime\n277: \n278: # Copy binary from builder\n279: COPY --from=builder /build/volcano-agent-scheduler /volcano-agent-scheduler\n280: \n281: # Copy default config\n282: COPY sandbox-orchestration/agent-scheduler.conf /config/agent-scheduler.conf\n283: \n284: # Set non-root user\n285: USER nonroot:nonroot\n286: \n287: # Set working directory\n288: WORKDIR /\n289: \n290: # Expose metrics port\n291: EXPOSE 8080\n292: \n293: # Health check\n294: HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n295:     CMD [\"/volcano-agent-scheduler\", \"--health\"]\n296: \n297: # Entrypoint\n298: ENTRYPOINT [\"/volcano-agent-scheduler\"]\n299: CMD [\"--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler\", \"--config=/config/agent-scheduler.conf\"]\n300: ```\n301: \n302: ### 6. Makefile Build Targets\n303: \n304: ```makefile\n305: # Makefile (add to root or docker/Makefile)\n306: \n307: # Docker build configuration\n308: DOCKER_REGISTRY ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh\n309: DOCKER_TAG ?= latest\n310: VERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty)\n311: COMMIT_SHA ?= $(shell git rev-parse --short HEAD)\n312: \n313: # Image names\n314: WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/workloadmanager\n315: ROUTER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/agentcube-router\n316: VOLCANO_SCHEDULER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/vc-agent-scheduler\n317: \n318: # Build targets\n319: .PHONY: docker-build\n320: docker-build: docker-build-workloadmanager docker-build-router docker-build-scheduler\n321: \n322: .PHONY: docker-build-workloadmanager\n323: docker-build-workloadmanager:\n324: \tdocker build \\\n325: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.workloadmanager \\\n326: \t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n327: \t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n328: \t\t.\n329: \n330: .PHONY: docker-build-router\n331: docker-build-router:\n332: \tdocker build \\\n333: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n334: \t\t-t $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n335: \t\t-t $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n336: \t\t.\n337: \n338: .PHONY: docker-build-scheduler\n339: docker-build-scheduler:\n340: \tdocker build \\\n341: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.volcano-agent-scheduler \\\n342: \t\t-t $(VOLCANO_SCHEDULER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n343: \t\t-t $(VOLCANO_SCHEDULER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n344: \t\t.\n345: \n346: .PHONY: docker-push\n347: docker-push: docker-push-workloadmanager docker-push-router docker-push-scheduler\n348: \n349: .PHONY: docker-push-workloadmanager\n350: docker-push-workloadmanager:\n351: \tdocker push $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n352: \tdocker push $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA)\n353: \n354: .PHONY: docker-push-router\n355: docker-push-router:\n356: \tdocker push $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n357: \tdocker push $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA)\n358: \n359: .PHONY: docker-push-scheduler\n360: docker-push-scheduler:\n361: \tdocker push $(VOLCANO_SCHEDULER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n362: \tdocker push $(VOLCANO_SCHEDULER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA)\n363: \n364: .PHONY: docker-validate\n365: docker-validate:\n366: \t./docker/validate.sh\n367: \n368: .PHONY: docker-clean\n369: docker-clean:\n370: \tdocker rmi $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n371: \tdocker rmi $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n372: \tdocker rmi $(VOLCANO_SCHEDULER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n373: ```\n374: \n375: ### 7. 镜像验证脚本\n376: \n377: ```bash\n378: #!/bin/bash\n379: # docker/validate.sh\n380: \n381: set -e\n382: \n383: WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE=\"${DOCKER_REGISTRY:-ghcr.io/volcano-sh}/workloadmanager:${DOCKER_TAG:-latest}\"\n384: ROUTER_IMAGE=\"${DOCKER_REGISTRY:-ghcr.io/volcano-sh}/agentcube-router:${DOCKER_TAG:-latest}\"\n385: VOLCANO_SCHEDULER_IMAGE=\"${DOCKER_REGISTRY:-ghcr.io/volcano-sh}/vc-agent-scheduler:${DOCKER_TAG:-latest}\"\n386: \n387: echo \"Validating Docker images...\"\n388: echo \"\"\n389: \n390: # Function to check image\n391: check_image() {\n392:     local image=$1\n393:     local name=$2\n394:     \n395:     echo \"Checking $name...\"\n396:     \n397:     # Check if image exists\n398:     if ! docker image inspect \"$image\" > /dev/null 2>&1; then\n399:         echo \"  ✗ Image not found: $image\"\n400:         return 1\n401:     fi\n402:     echo \"  ✓ Image exists\"\n403:     \n404:     # Check image size (should be < 50MB for distroless)\n405:     local size=$(docker image inspect \"$image\" --format='{{.Size}}')\n406:     local size_mb=$((size / 1024 / 1024))\n407:     if [ $size_mb -lt 50 ]; then\n408:         echo \"  ✓ Image size: ${size_mb}MB (< 50MB)\"\n409:     else\n410:         echo \"  ✗ Image size: ${size_mb}MB (>= 50MB)\"\n411:         return 1\n412:     fi\n413:     \n414:     # Check layer count (should be <= 5)\n415:     local layers=$(docker image history \"$image\" --format='{{.ID}}' | wc -l)\n416:     if [ $layers -le 5 ]; then\n417:         echo \"  ✓ Layer count: $layers (<= 5)\"\n418:     else\n419:         echo \"  ✗ Layer count: $layers (> 5)\"\n420:         return 1\n421:     fi\n422:     \n423:     # Check if running as non-root\n424:     local user=$(docker image inspect \"$image\" --format='{{.Config.User}}')\n425:     if [ -n \"$user\" ] && [ \"$user\" != \"root\" ]; then\n426:         echo \"  ✓ Running as non-root: $user\"\n427:     else\n428:         echo \"  ✗ Running as root or no user specified\"\n429:         return 1\n430:     fi\n431:     \n432:     # Check exposed ports\n433:     local ports=$(docker image inspect \"$image\" --format='{{json .Config.ExposedPorts}}')\n434:     if echo \"$ports\" | grep -q \"8080\"; then\n435:         echo \"  ✓ Port 8080 exposed\"\n436:     else\n437:         echo \"  ✗ Port 8080 not exposed\"\n438:         return 1\n439:     fi\n440:     \n441:     # Check health check\n442:     local healthcheck=$(docker image inspect \"$image\" --format='{{json .Config.Healthcheck}}')\n443:     if [ \"$healthcheck\" != \"null\" ] && [ -n \"$healthcheck\" ]; then\n444:         echo \"  ✓ Health check configured\"\n445:     else\n446:         echo \"  ✗ Health check not configured\"\n447:         return 1\n448:     fi\n449:     \n450:     echo \"\"\n451: }\n452: \n453: # Validate all images\n454: check_image \"$WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE\" \"Workload Manager\"\n455: check_image \"$ROUTER_IMAGE\" \"Router\"\n456: check_image \"$VOLCANO_SCHEDULER_IMAGE\" \"Volcano Agent Scheduler\"\n457: \n458: echo \"All validations passed!\"\n459: ```\n460: \n461: ### 8. 构建文档 (docker/README.md)\n462: \n463: ```markdown\n464: # Docker Image Builds\n465: \n466: AgentCube 控制平面组件的 Docker 镜像构建配置。\n467: \n468: ## 镜像列表\n469: \n470: | 组件 | 镜像名 | 端口 | 大小目标 |\n471: |------|--------|------|----------|\n472: | Workload Manager | ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager | 8080 | < 50MB |\n473: | Router | ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router | 8080 | < 50MB |\n474: | Volcano Agent Scheduler | ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler | 8080 | < 50MB |\n475: \n476: ## 快速开始\n477: \n478: ### 构建所有镜像\n479: \n480: ```bash\n481: make docker-build\n482: ```\n483: \n484: ### 构建单个镜像\n485: \n486: ```bash\n487: make docker-build-workloadmanager\n488: make docker-build-router\n489: make docker-build-scheduler\n490: ```\n491: \n492: ### 推送镜像\n493: \n494: ```bash\n495: make docker-push\n496: ```\n497: \n498: ### 验证镜像\n499: \n500: ```bash\n501: make docker-validate\n502: ```\n503: \n504: ## 自定义配置\n505: \n506: ### 修改镜像仓库\n507: \n508: ```bash\n509: export DOCKER_REGISTRY=myregistry.com\n510: make docker-build\n511: ```\n512: \n513: ### 修改镜像标签\n514: \n515: ```bash\n516: export DOCKER_TAG=v0.1.0\n517: make docker-build\n518: ```\n519: \n520: ## 多架构支持\n521: \n522: ```bash\n523: docker buildx build \\\n524:   --platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n525:   -t ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:latest \\\n526:   --push \\\n527:   -f docker/Dockerfile.workloadmanager \\\n528:   .\n529: ```\n530: \n531: ## 安全最佳实践\n532: \n533: 1. **非 root 用户** - 所有镜像以 nonroot 用户运行\n534: 2. **Distroless 基础** - 使用 distroless/static-debian11 减少攻击面\n535: 3. **多阶段构建** - 仅复制必需的二进制文件\n536: 4. **静态链接** - CGO_ENABLED=0 避免动态库依赖\n537: 5. **健康检查** - 配置 HEALTHCHECK 指令\n538: \n539: ## 故障排查\n540: \n541: ### 镜像构建失败\n542: \n543: 检查 Go 代码是否能编译：\n544: ```bash\n545: go build -o /tmp/test ./cmd/agentcube\n546: ```\n547: \n548: ### 镜像过大\n549: \n550: 检查是否包含了不必要的文件：\n551: ```bash\n552: docker history <image-name>\n553: ```\n554: \n555: ### 权限错误\n556: \n557: 确保 Docker daemon 正常运行：\n558: ```bash\n559: docker info\n560: ```\n561: ```\n562: \n563: ## Impact Analysis\n564: \n565: ### 依赖影响\n566: \n567: | 依赖项 | 版本 | 用途 |\n568: |--------|------|------|\n569: | Docker | ≥20.10 | 镜像构建 |\n570: | Go | ≥1.21 | 应用编译 |\n571: | Make | 任意 | 构建自动化 |\n572: \n573: ### 模块依赖关系\n574: \n575: ```\n576: docker/\n577: ├── .dockerignore                       # 无依赖\n578: ├── Dockerfile.workloadmanager          # 依赖 cmd/agentcube, pkg/\n579: ├── Dockerfile.router                   # 依赖 cmd/agentcube-proxy, pkg/\n580: ├── Dockerfile.volcano-agent-scheduler  # 依赖 cmd/agentd, pkg/\n581: ├── Makefile                            # 依赖所有 Dockerfile\n582: ├── validate.sh                         # 依赖 docker CLI\n583: └── README.md                           # 文档\n584: ```\n585: \n586: ### 向后兼容性\n587: \n588: - 首次实现，无破坏性变更风险\n589: - 镜像标签策略支持版本追溯\n590: - 多架构支持未来扩展\n591: \n592: ### 测试影响\n593: \n594: - 需要验证镜像构建成功\n595: - 需要验证镜像大小符合目标\n596: - 需要验证容器可正常启动\n597: - 需要验证健康检查有效\n598: \n599: ## Alternatives Considered\n600: \n601: ### 方案 1: 单 Dockerfile 多目标构建\n602: \n603: **优点:**\n604: - 单一文件，易于维护\n605: - 使用 BUILDKIT 多目标\n606: \n607: **缺点:**\n608: - 文件过大，难以阅读\n609: - 不便于独立构建\n610: \n611: **决策:** 采用独立 Dockerfile，每个组件一个文件。\n612: \n613: ### 方案 2: 使用 Alpine 基础镜像\n614: \n615: **优点:**\n616: - 镜像体积小\n617: - 包管理方便\n618: \n619: **缺点:**\n620: - 存在已知安全漏洞\n621: - glibc 兼容性问题\n622: \n623: **决策:** 采用 distroless/static-debian11，更安全。\n624: \n625: ### 方案 3: 单一巨型镜像（包含所有组件）\n626: \n627: **优点:**\n628: - 单一镜像，部署简单\n629: - 减少镜像数量\n630: \n631: **缺点:**\n632: - 镜像体积大\n633: - 安全风险高\n634: - 无法独立部署组件\n635: \n636: **决策:** 采用独立镜像，支持最小化部署。\n637: \n638: ### 方案 4: 使用 Buildpacks\n639: \n640: **优点:**\n641: - 自动化程度高\n642: - 无需 Dockerfile\n643: \n644: **缺点:**\n645: - 定制化能力弱\n646: - 无法精确控制镜像内容\n647: \n648: **决策:** 采用 Dockerfile，保持完全控制。\n649: \n650: ## Testing Strategy\n651: \n652: ### 构建测试\n653: \n654: 1. **本地构建测试** - 验证所有 Dockerfile 可成功构建\n655: 2. **镜像大小测试** - 验证镜像体积 < 50MB\n656: 3. **层数测试** - 验证镜像层数 <= 5\n657: \n658: ### 功能测试\n659: \n660: 1. **容器启动测试** - 验证容器可正常启动\n661: 2. **健康检查测试** - 验证 HEALTHCHECK 有效\n662: 3. **端口暴露测试** - 验证 8080 端口可访问\n663: \n664: ### 安全测试\n665: \n666: 1. **非 root 测试** - 验证容器以非 root 用户运行\n667: 2. **漏洞扫描** - 使用 Trivy 扫描镜像漏洞\n668: 3. **最小权限测试** - 验证容器无多余权限\n669: \n670: ### 测试覆盖目标\n671: \n672: - Dockerfile: 100%（所有指令正确）\n673: - 构建脚本：100%（所有目标有效）\n674: - 验证脚本：100%（所有检查项通过）\n675: \n676: ## Acceptance Criteria\n677: \n678: - [ ] Workload Manager Dockerfile 可成功构建\n679: - [ ] Router Dockerfile 可成功构建\n680: - [ ] Volcano Agent Scheduler Dockerfile 可成功构建\n681: - [ ] 镜像大小 < 50MB\n682: - [ ] 镜像层数 <= 5\n683: - [ ] 容器以非 root 用户运行\n684: - [ ] 健康检查配置正确\n685: - [ ] 端口 8080 暴露\n686: - [ ] Makefile 构建目标可用\n687: - [ ] 验证脚本通过所有检查\n688: - [ ] 文档完整（构建说明、故障排查）\n689: \n690: ## Dependencies\n691: \n692: ### 必需依赖\n693: - Docker ≥20.10\n694: - Go ≥1.21\n695: - Make\n696: \n697: ### 可选依赖\n698: - Docker Buildx（多架构支持）\n699: - Trivy（安全扫描）\n700: \n701: ### 被依赖\n702: - AR-030 (Helm Chart) - 镜像用于 Helm Chart 部署\n703: - cmd/agentcube, cmd/agentcube-proxy, cmd/agentd - 应用源码\n704: \n705: ## Migration Notes\n706: \n707: ### 从手动构建迁移\n708: \n709: 1. 安装 Docker 和 Go 1.21+\n710: 2. 运行 `make docker-build` 构建镜像\n711: 3. 验证镜像 `make docker-validate`\n712: 4. 更新 Helm values.yaml 使用新镜像\n713: \n714: ### 破坏性变更\n715: 无 - 首次实现。\n716: \n717: ### 行为变更\n718: - 从源码编译改为容器化部署\n719: - 从直接运行改为容器运行\n720: \n721: ## Open Questions\n722: \n723: 1. 是否需要支持 Windows 容器？（未来扩展）\n724: 2. 是否需要集成镜像签名？（待需求明确）\n725: 3. 是否需要支持自定义基础镜像？（待需求明确）\n726: \n727: ## References\n728: \n729: - `deployment/spec.md` - 部署规范\n730: - `deployment/design.md` - 部署设计\n731: - `cmd/agentcube/` - Workload Manager 源码\n732: - `cmd/agentcube-proxy/` - Router 源码\n733: - `cmd/agentd/` - Volcano Agent Scheduler 源码\n734: - Docker Best Practices: https://docs.docker.com/develop/develop-images/dockerfile_best-practices/\n735: - Distroless Images: https://github.com/GoogleContainerTools/distroless\n\n(End of file - total 735 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n\n## Purpose\n\n本提案实现 AgentCube 项目的 Dockerfile 多阶段构建，为 Workload Manager、Router、Volcano Agent Scheduler 三个核心组件提供独立的容器镜像构建能力。该 Dockerfile 是 AgentCube 控制平面组件容器化的基础，支撑 Helm Chart 部署和 Kubernetes 运行时环境。\n\n目标是：\n\n1. **多阶段构建优化** - 使用多阶段构建减少最终镜像体积，仅包含运行必需的二进制文件和配置\n2. **三镜像分离** - 为 Workload Manager、Router、Volcano Agent Scheduler 分别构建独立镜像，支持差异化部署\n3. **最小化攻击面** - 基于 distroless 或 alpine 基础镜像，减少安全漏洞风险\n4. **构建可复用** - 统一的 Dockerfile 模板支持本地构建、CI/CD 流水线、多架构支持\n5. **环境一致性** - 确保开发、测试、生产环境的镜像构建行为一致\n6. **版本可追溯** - 镜像标签与 Git commit/Tag 关联，支持版本追踪和回滚\n\n本提案基于 deployment/design.md 和 deployment/spec.md 的规范，遵循 Docker 多阶段构建最佳实践。\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** docker  ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775881416967,"end":1775881417003}}}}
