{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881520428,"sessionID":"ses_285386450ffeByI5JDjYc05Ahx","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac812ee001lO92CQUx03x7aL","messageID":"msg_d7ac80947001oDimeY2KzKH9z0","sessionID":"ses_285386450ffeByI5JDjYc05Ahx","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_d2141abbd3fc42369007b7c8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/design.md","content":"# Docker Multi-Stage Build Design — AR-032\n\n**Module:** `docker`  \n**Language:** Dockerfile  \n**Size:** S  \n**Stage:** ST-1 completed\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation details for Docker multi-stage builds for three AgentCube components: Workload Manager, Router, and picod. The design follows container security best practices, optimizes for minimal image size, and ensures consistency across development, testing, and production environments.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Multi-Stage Build Pattern\n\nEach component uses a two-stage Dockerfile:\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Stage 1: Builder                   │\n│  - Base: golang:1.21-alpine         │\n│  - Downloads Go modules             │\n│  - Compiles static binary           │\n│  - CGO_ENABLED=0                    │\n└─────────────────────────────────────┘\n                  │\n                  ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Stage 2: Runtime                   │\n│  - Base: alpine:3.19                │\n│  - Copies binary from builder       │\n│  - Non-root user (UID 1000)         │\n│  - Exposes port 8080                │\n└─────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Mapping\n\n| Component | Dockerfile | Source Path | Binary Output | Runtime User |\n|-----------|------------|-------------|---------------|--------------|\n| Workload Manager | `docker/Dockerfile` | `./cmd/workload-manager` | `/workloadmanager` | `apiserver` (UID 1000) |\n| Router | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | `./cmd/router` | `/router` | `router` (UID 1000) |\n| Picod | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | `./cmd/picod` | `/picod` | `picod` (UID 1000) |\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Docker Build Arguments\n\n```dockerfile\n# Common to all Dockerfiles\nARG GO_VERSION=1.21\nARG ALPINE_VERSION=3.19\nARG TARGETARCH=amd64\nARG TARGETOS=linux\n```\n\n### OCI Image Labels\n\n```dockerfile\n# Applied to all images\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.title=\"<component>\"\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.description=\"AgentCube <component> component\"\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.vendor=\"AgentCube\"\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.version=\"<version>\"\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.revision=\"<commit-sha>\"\n```\n\n### Environment Variables (Runtime)\n\n| Variable | Component | Purpose | Required |\n|----------|-----------|---------|----------|\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Workload Manager, Router | Redis server address | Yes |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Workload Manager, Router | Redis authentication | No (default: \"\") |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Router | Workload Manager endpoint | Yes |\n| `PORT` | All | HTTP listen port | No (default: 8080) |\n| `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | All | Kubernetes namespace | No (auto-injected via fieldRef) |\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Docker Build Interface\n\n**Build Command:**\n```bash\ndocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.<component> -t <image-name>:<tag> .\n```\n\n**Build Context:** Repository root\n\n**Required Files in Context:**\n- `go.mod`, `go.sum`\n- `cmd/<component>/`\n- `pkg/`\n\n**Excluded Files (via `.dockerignore`):**\n- `.git/`\n- `bin/`, `pkg/` (build artifacts)\n- `*_test.go`\n- `*.md` (documentation)\n- `testing/`\n- `.pytest_cache/`, `__pycache__/`\n\n### Container Runtime Interface\n\n**Exposed Port:** 8080 (all components)\n\n**Entrypoint:**\n- Workload Manager: `/workloadmanager`\n- Router: `/router`\n- Picod: `/picod`\n\n**Default CMD:**\n- Workload Manager: `[\"--port=8080\"]`\n- Router: `[\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]`\n- Picod: `[\"--port=8080\"]`\n\n**Health Check:**\n```dockerfile\nHEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n    CMD wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Build-Time Errors\n\n| Error | Cause | Resolution |\n|-------|-------|------------|\n| `go.mod not found` | Build context incorrect | Ensure build runs from repository root |\n| `build failed: package not found` | Source path mismatch | Verify `cmd/` and `pkg/` are in context |\n| `out of memory` | Insufficient builder resources | Increase Docker memory limit |\n| `COPY failed: file not found` | `.dockerignore` excludes required file | Review `.dockerignore` patterns |\n\n### Runtime Errors\n\n| Error | Cause | Resolution |\n|-------|-------|------------|\n| `permission denied` | Running as root when non-root expected | Ensure `USER` directive is applied |\n| `port already in use` | Port 8080 occupied | Override `PORT` environment variable |\n| `connection refused to Redis` | `REDIS_ADDR` not set or incorrect | Verify environment variable configuration |\n| `binary not found` | Build stage failed to produce binary | Check builder stage logs |\n\n### Validation Failures\n\nThe `validate.sh` script shall fail with non-zero exit code when:\n- Image size ≥ 50MB\n- Layer count > 5\n- Running as root user\n- Port 8080 not exposed\n- Health check not configured\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests (Dockerfile Syntax)\n\n**Test File:** `docker/Dockerfile.test` (optional linting stage)\n\n**Test Cases:**\n1. All Dockerfiles pass `hadolint` validation\n2. No hardcoded secrets in any layer\n3. Base images use pinned versions (not `latest`)\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**Test Script:** `docker/test/build_test.sh`\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# Build all images and verify basic properties\n\nset -e\n\nIMAGES=(\n    \"workloadmanager:test\"\n    \"router:test\"\n    \"picod:test\"\n)\n\nfor image in \"${IMAGES[@]}\"; do\n    echo \"Building $image...\"\n    docker build -f \"docker/Dockerfile.${image%%:*}\" -t \"$image\" .\n    \n    # Verify image exists\n    docker image inspect \"$image\" > /dev/null\n    \n    echo \"✓ $image built successfully\"\ndone\n```\n\n### Container Runtime Tests\n\n**Test Script:** `docker/test/runtime_test.sh`\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# Test container runtime behavior\n\nset -e\n\ntest_container() {\n    local image=$1\n    local name=$2\n    \n    # Start container\n    docker run -d --name \"$name\" \"$image\"\n    \n    # Wait for health check\n    sleep 10\n    \n    # Check running status\n    if ! docker inspect --format='{{.State.Running}}' \"$name\" | grep -q true; then\n        echo \"✗ $name failed to start\"\n        docker logs \"$name\"\n        return 1\n    fi\n    \n    # Check non-root user\n    local user=$(docker exec \"$name\" id -u)\n    if [ \"$user\" != \"1000\" ]; then\n        echo \"✗ $name running as root (UID: $user)\"\n        return 1\n    fi\n    \n    # Cleanup\n    docker stop \"$name\" && docker rm \"$name\"\n    \n    echo \"✓ $name passed runtime tests\"\n}\n\ntest_container \"workloadmanager:test\" \"wm-test\"\ntest_container \"router:test\" \"router-test\"\ntest_container \"picod:test\" \"picod-test\"\n```\n\n### Security Tests\n\n**Tool:** Trivy (optional)\n\n```bash\n# Scan for vulnerabilities\ntrivy image workloadmanager:latest --severity HIGH,CRITICAL --exit-code 1\ntrivy image router:latest --severity HIGH,CRITICAL --exit-code 1\ntrivy image picod:latest --severity HIGH,CRITICAL --exit-code 1\n```\n\n### Performance Tests\n\n**Metrics to Validate:**\n- Build time < 5 minutes per image (with cached dependencies)\n- Image size < 50MB per image\n- Layer count ≤ 5\n- Container start time < 2 seconds\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Workload Manager Dockerfile\n\n```dockerfile\n# docker/Dockerfile\n# Multi-stage build for Workload Manager\n\n# Stage 1: Builder\nFROM golang:1.21-alpine AS builder\n\nWORKDIR /build\n\n# Cache Go modules\nCOPY go.mod go.sum ./\nRUN go mod download\n\n# Copy source code\nCOPY cmd/workload-manager ./cmd/workload-manager\nCOPY pkg ./pkg\n\n# Build static binary\nRUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build \\\n    -ldflags=\"-w -s\" \\\n    -o /build/workloadmanager \\\n    ./cmd/workload-manager\n\n# Stage 2: Runtime\nFROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime\n\n# Install CA certificates for HTTPS\nRUN apk --no-cache add ca-certificates\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Copy binary from builder\nCOPY --from=builder /build/workloadmanager /app/workloadmanager\n\n# Create non-root user\nRUN adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver\n\n# Set ownership\nRUN chown -R apiserver:apiserver /app\n\n# Switch to non-root user\nUSER apiserver\n\n# Expose port\nEXPOSE 8080\n\n# Health check\nHEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n    CMD wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1\n\n# Labels\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.title=\"workloadmanager\"\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.description=\"AgentCube Workload Manager component\"\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.vendor=\"AgentCube\"\n\n# Entrypoint\nENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]\nCMD [\"--port=8080\"]\n```\n\n### Router Dockerfile\n\n```dockerfile\n# docker/Dockerfile.router\n# Multi-stage build for Router\n\n# Stage 1: Builder\nFROM golang:1.21-alpine AS builder\n\nWORKDIR /build\n\n# Cache Go modules\nCOPY go.mod go.sum ./\nRUN go mod download\n\n# Copy source code\nCOPY cmd/router ./cmd/router\nCOPY pkg ./pkg\n\n# Build static binary\nRUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build \\\n    -ldflags=\"-w -s\" \\\n    -o /build/router \\\n    ./cmd/router\n\n# Stage 2: Runtime\nFROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime\n\nRUN apk --no-cache add ca-certificates\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\nCOPY --from=builder /build/router /app/router\n\nRUN adduser -D -u 1000 router\nRUN chown -R router:router /app\n\nUSER router\n\nEXPOSE 8080\n\nHEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n    CMD wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1\n\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.title=\"router\"\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.description=\"AgentCube Router component\"\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.vendor=\"AgentCube\"\n\nENTRYPOINT [\"/app/router\"]\nCMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]\n```\n\n### Picod Dockerfile\n\n```dockerfile\n# docker/Dockerfile.picod\n# Multi-stage build for Picod\n\n# Stage 1: Builder\nFROM golang:1.21-alpine AS builder\n\nWORKDIR /build\n\nCOPY go.mod go.sum ./\nRUN go mod download\n\nCOPY cmd/picod ./cmd/picod\nCOPY pkg ./pkg\n\nRUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build \\\n    -ldflags=\"-w -s\" \\\n    -o /build/picod \\\n    ./cmd/picod\n\n# Stage 2: Runtime\nFROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime\n\nRUN apk --no-cache add ca-certificates\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\nCOPY --from=builder /build/picod /app/picod\n\nRUN adduser -D -u 1000 picod\nRUN chown -R picod:picod /app\n\nUSER picod\n\nEXPOSE 8080\n\nHEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n    CMD wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1\n\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.title=\"picod\"\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.description=\"AgentCube Picod component\"\nLABEL org.opencontainers.image.vendor=\"AgentCube\"\n\nENTRYPOINT [\"/app/picod\"]\nCMD [\"--port=8080\"]\n```\n\n### .dockerignore\n\n```dockerignore\n# .dockerignore\n# Build context exclusions for efficient Docker builds\n\n# Version control\n.git\n.gitignore\n\n# Build artifacts\nbin/\ndist/\n*.out\ncoverage.out\n\n# Dependencies (Go modules cached during build)\nvendor/\n\n# IDE and editor files\n.idea/\n.vscode/\n*.swp\n*.swo\n*~\n\n# Documentation\n*.md\n!README.md\n\n# Tests\ntesting/\n*_test.go\n.pytest_cache/\n\n# Docker (avoid recursive copy)\ndocker/\nDockerfile*\n\n# Kubernetes manifests\nmanifests/\nchanges/\n\n# Python artifacts\n__pycache__/\n*.pyc\n*.pyo\n.eggs/\n*.egg-info/\n\n# OS files\n.DS_Store\nThumbs.db\n\n# Logs\n*.log\nlogs/\n\n# Temporary files\ntmp/\ntemp/\n```\n\n---\n\n## Makefile Integration\n\n### Build Targets\n\n```makefile\n# Docker configuration\nDOCKER_REGISTRY ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh\nDOCKER_TAG ?= latest\nVERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo \"dev\")\nCOMMIT_SHA ?= $(shell git rev-parse --short HEAD 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")\n\n# Image names\nWORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/workloadmanager\nROUTER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/router\nPICOD_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/picod\n\n# Build all images\n.PHONY: docker-build-all\ndocker-build-all: docker-build-workloadmanager docker-build-router docker-build-picod\n\n# Build Workload Manager image\n.PHONY: docker-build-workloadmanager\ndocker-build-workloadmanager:\n\t@echo \"Building Workload Manager image...\"\n\tdocker build \\\n\t\t-f docker/Dockerfile \\\n\t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n\t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n\t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(VERSION) \\\n\t\t.\n\t@echo \"✓ Workload Manager image built: $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\"\n\n# Build Router image\n.PHONY: docker-build-router\ndocker-build-router:\n\t@echo \"Building Router image...\"\n\tdocker build \\\n\t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n\t\t-t $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n\t\t-t $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n\t\t-t $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(VERSION) \\\n\t\t.\n\t@echo \"✓ Router image built: $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\"\n\n# Build Picod image\n.PHONY: docker-build-picod\ndocker-build-picod:\n\t@echo \"Building Picod image...\"\n\tdocker build \\\n\t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.picod \\\n\t\t-t $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n\t\t-t $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n\t\t-t $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(VERSION) \\\n\t\t.\n\t@echo \"✓ Picod image built: $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\"\n\n# Push all images\n.PHONY: docker-push-all\ndocker-push-all: docker-push-workloadmanager docker-push-router docker-push-picod\n\n# Push Workload Manager image\n.PHONY: docker-push-workloadmanager\ndocker-push-workloadmanager:\n\t@echo \"Pushing Workload Manager image to $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)...\"\n\tdocker push $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n\tdocker push $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA)\n\tdocker push $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(VERSION)\n\n# Push Router image\n.PHONY: docker-push-router\ndocker-push-router:\n\t@echo \"Pushing Router image to $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)...\"\n\tdocker push $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n\tdocker push $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA)\n\tdocker push $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(VERSION)\n\n# Push Picod image\n.PHONY: docker-push-picod\ndocker-push-picod:\n\t@echo \"Pushing Picod image to $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)...\"\n\tdocker push $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n\tdocker push $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA)\n\tdocker push $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(VERSION)\n\n# Load images to Kind cluster\n.PHONY: kind-load-all\nkind-load-all: kind-load-workloadmanager kind-load-router kind-load-picod\n\n.PHONY: kind-load-workloadmanager\nkind-load-workloadmanager:\n\tkind load docker-image $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n\n.PHONY: kind-load-router\nkind-load-router:\n\tkind load docker-image $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n\n.PHONY: kind-load-picod\nkind-load-picod:\n\tkind load docker-image $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n\n# Multi-architecture build (requires Docker Buildx)\n.PHONY: docker-buildx-all\ndocker-buildx-all: docker-buildx-workloadmanager docker-buildx-router docker-buildx-picod\n\n.PHONY: docker-buildx-workloadmanager\ndocker-buildx-workloadmanager:\n\tdocker buildx build \\\n\t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n\t\t-f docker/Dockerfile \\\n\t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n\t\t--push \\\n\t\t.\n\n.PHONY: docker-buildx-router\ndocker-buildx-router:\n\tdocker buildx build \\\n\t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n\t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n\t\t-t $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n\t\t--push \\\n\t\t.\n\n.PHONY: docker-buildx-picod\ndocker-buildx-picod:\n\tdocker buildx build \\\n\t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n\t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.picod \\\n\t\t-t $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n\t\t--push \\\n\t\t.\n\n# Clean up local images\n.PHONY: docker-clean\ndocker-clean:\n\t-docker rmi $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n\t-docker rmi $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) 2>/dev/null || true\n\t-docker rmi $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n\t-docker rmi $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) 2>/dev/null || true\n\t-docker rmi $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n\t-docker rmi $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) 2>/dev/null || true\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\ndeployment/docker/\n├── Dockerfile                 # Workload Manager image\n├── Dockerfile.router          # Router image\n├── Dockerfile.picod           # Picod image\n├── .dockerignore              # Build context exclusions\n├── design.md                  # This file\n├── delta-spec.md              # Delta specification\n└── test/\n    ├── build_test.sh          # Build integration tests\n    └── runtime_test.sh        # Container runtime tests\n```\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Principle of Least Privilege\n\n1. **Non-root execution:** All containers run as UID 1000 (non-root)\n2. **Minimal capabilities:** No `--cap-add` required\n3. **Read-only root filesystem:** Compatible with `securityContext.readOnlyRootFilesystem: true`\n\n### Supply Chain Security\n\n1. **Pinned base images:** Use specific versions (`golang:1.21-alpine`, `alpine:3.19`)\n2. **No secrets in images:** Credentials injected via Kubernetes Secrets/Environment\n3. **Reproducible builds:** Static linking with `CGO_ENABLED=0`\n\n### Attack Surface Reduction\n\n1. **Minimal runtime:** Alpine 3.19 has ~5MB attack surface\n2. **No shell access:** Optional hardening via `rm -rf /bin/sh` in runtime stage\n3. **Static binaries:** No dynamic library vulnerabilities\n\n---\n\n## Performance Optimization\n\n### Build Cache Optimization\n\n1. **Layer ordering:** Copy `go.mod`/`go.sum` before source code\n2. **Module caching:** `go mod download` runs before code changes\n3. **Context exclusion:** `.dockerignore` reduces build context size\n\n### Image Size Optimization\n\n1. **Multi-stage build:** Build tools excluded from runtime\n2. **Static compilation:** No glibc dependencies\n3. **Minimal base:** Alpine 3.19 (~5MB) vs Debian (~100MB)\n\nExpected image sizes:\n- Workload Manager: ~25-35MB\n- Router: ~25-35MB\n- Picod: ~25-35MB\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. **Multi-architecture support:** Should ARM64 builds be mandatory or optional?\n2. **Distroless migration:** Should we migrate from Alpine to `gcr.io/distroless/static-debian11` for enhanced security?\n3. **Version injection:** Should build version/commit be injected into binaries via `-ldflags`?\n4. **Health check endpoint:** Should HEALTHCHECK use a dedicated endpoint or the main `/health`?\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- `deployment/spec.md` — Deployment Specification\n- `deployment/design.md` — Deployment Design\n- `docker/delta-spec.md` — Delta Specification for AR-032\n- Docker Best Practices: https://docs.docker.com/develop/develop-images/dockerfile_best-practices/\n- Alpine Linux: https://alpinelinux.org/\n- Multi-stage builds: https://docs.docker.com/build/building/multi-stage/\n\n(End of file)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/design.md","time":{"start":1775881520415,"end":1775881520425}}}}
